04:00.035 --> 04:02.912
...trying to figure out what makes
you happy, who you kidding?

04:03.080 --> 04:05.206
Oh, yeah. Maybe that's it.

04:05.374 --> 04:06.666
Yeah, maybe.

04:06.834 --> 04:09.627
- Swiggy?
- Lord, please let my car be fixed today.

04:09.795 --> 04:11.629
Oh, dear.

04:27.104 --> 04:28.146
Hey, who's that?

04:31.191 --> 04:33.192
She looks a little young.

04:33.360 --> 04:35.403
- Hold this.
- What are you gonna do?

04:35.571 --> 04:39.323
You know how I say if they're old enough
to crawl, they're in the right position.

04:39.491 --> 04:41.993
What are you gonna do?
What are you gonna do? You crazy.

04:47.541 --> 04:50.376
- Whoo! Yeah! Fifty points!
- Ha-ha-ha.

04:50.544 --> 04:51.878
Yeah, you good, boy.

04:53.213 --> 04:54.672
Shut up!

04:55.090 --> 04:57.175
- Daddy!
- Hey!

05:00.471 --> 05:02.096
- Shut up.
- Daddy!

05:02.264 --> 05:04.223
Shut up.

05:04.808 --> 05:06.267
- I'll kill you.
- My turn.

05:08.937 --> 05:11.230
- Daddy!
- Shut up.

05:11.565 --> 05:13.399
Daddy.

05:16.320 --> 05:17.695
Yeah.

05:21.200 --> 05:22.366
Mom! Mama!

05:22.534 --> 05:25.161
Mom! Mama!

05:25.329 --> 05:27.079
Mom!

05:30.292 --> 05:32.168
Mama!

05:33.045 --> 05:34.587
Mom.

05:36.924 --> 05:39.133
- What is this?
- Groceries.

05:39.301 --> 05:42.094
- Y'all didn't see her?
- No, ma'am.

05:50.604 --> 05:52.146
Carl Lee! Stop!

05:52.314 --> 05:55.775
- You got a call from your wife!
- What? What?

06:23.262 --> 06:25.346
How many appointments
do we have today, Ethel?

06:25.514 --> 06:27.765
Not a one.

06:28.141 --> 06:31.102
But it is the 1st of the month again
and guess what.

06:31.270 --> 06:35.523
The checks are pouring in and we have
enough money to pay all our past debts.

06:35.691 --> 06:38.109
That'll be your last drink.

06:38.277 --> 06:41.404
Just keep us no more than
one month behind on any vendor, please.

06:41.572 --> 06:43.447
Why, you have been drinking.

06:43.615 --> 06:44.657
Two months.

06:44.825 --> 06:46.909
Well, these are the most delinquent.

06:47.077 --> 06:49.245
The rent's in there.

06:49.413 --> 06:54.709
I appreciate the practice, capitÃ¡n, I do,
but you could've left me a couple of clients.

07:02.009 --> 07:04.510
Baby, here's Daddy.

07:08.682 --> 07:11.058
Oh, no.

07:13.478 --> 07:16.689
I'm here, baby. Daddy's here.

07:16.857 --> 07:20.693
Daddy, I'm sorry I dropped the groceries.

07:20.861 --> 07:24.697
- That's all right, baby. It's all right, baby.
- I'm sorry, Daddy.

07:24.865 --> 07:26.699
That's all right.

07:52.726 --> 07:54.310
Look at this.

08:21.963 --> 08:23.047
Billy Ray?

08:23.882 --> 08:28.552
Sorry, sir, but we don't allow
no African-Americans in here. Ha, ha.

08:28.720 --> 08:31.722
Billy Ray Cobb, you and Mr. Willard
need to come with me.

08:32.640 --> 08:34.100
Hell, no. I ain't moving.

08:34.267 --> 08:37.311
- You know that little girl you took for a ride?
- Mm.

08:37.479 --> 08:40.731
- What little girl?
- I got bad news for you. She didn't die.

08:41.107 --> 08:45.194
So unless there's another redneck asshole
got a souped-up yellow pickup...

08:45.362 --> 08:47.780
...with a Confederate flag
in the windshield--

08:47.948 --> 08:51.409
Blue gums, why don't you take your
black ass out of here and grab a branch.

08:51.576 --> 08:55.621
Unless you got an explanation for what
this was doing in the bed of your truck...

08:56.623 --> 08:59.125
...you're going to jail. Now, get up.

09:00.168 --> 09:02.128
You can go to hell, nigger.

09:02.295 --> 09:04.755
- Unh! Goddamn!
- Hey!

09:08.969 --> 09:11.887
Now, you earned
the right to remain silent.

09:12.347 --> 09:15.099
- Here you go, just the way you like them.
- Thank you.

09:15.267 --> 09:17.935
- Dell, sugar, today I'm gonna have--
- Go to hell, Harry.

09:18.103 --> 09:20.521
On second thought,
I'm just gonna watch baby eat his.

09:20.689 --> 09:22.732
I am not the one
who handled her divorce.

09:22.899 --> 09:24.817
Can't she see
I'm shriveling away here?

09:24.985 --> 09:26.444
I'm shriveling.

09:26.611 --> 09:29.238
- Say, Jake?
- Yeah, what's up, Dwayne?

09:29.906 --> 09:32.825
Didn't you defend Billy Ray Cobb
few years back?

09:34.161 --> 09:36.203
What kind of case was it?

09:36.371 --> 09:37.830
Caught him selling dope.

09:37.998 --> 09:40.166
Spent time in Parchman.
Got out last year.

09:40.834 --> 09:43.419
No, I think some Memphis lawyer
handled that.

09:43.587 --> 09:45.254
Why do you ask?

09:45.422 --> 09:48.007
Well, we picked him up for rape.
Him and Pete Willard.

09:48.175 --> 09:49.341
Who'd they rape?

09:50.969 --> 09:52.511
You know Carl Lee Hailey?

09:52.888 --> 09:54.805
Sure, I defended his brother Lester.

09:57.058 --> 09:58.893
It was his little girl.

10:01.938 --> 10:03.063
Little Tonya?

10:04.483 --> 10:06.233
Yeah.

10:08.528 --> 10:09.612
How old is she?

10:11.281 --> 10:12.865
She's 10.

10:55.450 --> 10:58.327
Mr. Willard, I'm Sheriff Ozzie Walls.

10:59.037 --> 11:01.705
My mama voted for you.

11:03.208 --> 11:05.251
I seen you play for the Rams.

11:07.546 --> 11:11.298
Way I figure, a nigger sheriff's okay,
been on TV and all.

11:14.219 --> 11:15.511
No offense.

11:18.849 --> 11:20.349
What's your full name?

11:20.517 --> 11:22.935
James Lewis Willard.

11:26.439 --> 11:30.025
Four, which is a difference of 110.60.

11:33.446 --> 11:35.281
Who's there?

11:54.134 --> 11:55.968
Carl Lee.

12:01.433 --> 12:03.225
How is she?

12:04.185 --> 12:06.312
She holding on.

12:07.314 --> 12:10.107
Doctor says she ain't
out of the woods yet, though.

12:17.657 --> 12:20.367
They worked her over
something good, Jake.

12:27.834 --> 12:32.254
You remember them four white boys raped
that little black girl in the Delta last year?

12:34.758 --> 12:35.841
Yeah.

12:36.009 --> 12:37.843
They, uh....

12:38.011 --> 12:39.553
They got off, didn't they?

12:41.932 --> 12:43.432
Yeah.

12:48.104 --> 12:50.064
Jake....

12:50.523 --> 12:53.192
I was in a jam, you'd help me out,
wouldn't you?

12:55.445 --> 12:57.363
Sure, Carl Lee.

12:59.574 --> 13:01.408
What kind of jam you talking about?

13:02.452 --> 13:04.745
You got a daughter, Jake.

13:04.913 --> 13:06.789
What would you do?

13:17.467 --> 13:19.426
Dream some good dreams, baby girl.

13:19.761 --> 13:22.221
Good night, Daddy.

13:22.514 --> 13:24.390
Night, baby.

13:40.073 --> 13:42.116
- Is she asleep?
- Yeah.

13:42.325 --> 13:45.035
- Is she the sweetest thing?
- Yeah, she is.

13:45.203 --> 13:47.204
Next to you.

13:47.747 --> 13:52.251
Tell you what, I look at her, though, and
I cannot help but think about little Tonya.

13:53.920 --> 13:55.587
Don't.

13:58.425 --> 14:00.509
Don't do that to yourself.

14:01.261 --> 14:02.344
Yeah.

14:06.558 --> 14:07.599
Something else wrong?

14:09.060 --> 14:11.020
Tonya's father...

14:11.187 --> 14:13.272
...Carl Lee Hailey...

14:13.440 --> 14:14.773
...came by the office today.

14:17.027 --> 14:19.778
Man's heart is torn wide open, baby.

14:19.946 --> 14:21.530
I don't know, but...

14:21.698 --> 14:24.533
...sounded to me
like he was thinking about doing something.

14:24.701 --> 14:25.743
Like what?

14:27.454 --> 14:29.496
Something like maybe
killing those two boys.

14:30.123 --> 14:31.457
Was he serious?

14:35.420 --> 14:37.629
I don't know. I don't know.

14:37.797 --> 14:40.466
It could've been just the hurt talking,
you know?

14:40.967 --> 14:44.636
But when you think that it's possible
that those two animals could...

14:44.804 --> 14:46.680
...go free...

14:47.599 --> 14:49.975
...and be walking the streets....

14:52.479 --> 14:54.104
I....

14:54.856 --> 14:56.148
I don't know.

14:58.151 --> 15:02.029
After what that man has been through,
he's probably capable of anything.

15:03.323 --> 15:05.741
Somebody should do something.

15:06.326 --> 15:07.993
You should call Sheriff Walls.

15:09.579 --> 15:11.163
Yeah.

16:06.594 --> 16:09.763
To release the owner from assessment.

16:13.143 --> 16:17.563
I hope I'm having a heart attack
because then I'd get to sue you.

16:17.730 --> 16:20.399
Don't stand on ceremony, come on in.

16:20.567 --> 16:22.568
What? No clients?

16:22.735 --> 16:25.571
Just waiting to pick yours up
on appeal, Harry.

16:25.738 --> 16:29.074
And you, are you on vacation?

16:29.659 --> 16:31.785
Fortunately for me, my lovely...

16:31.953 --> 16:34.246
...divorce doesn't go on vacation.

16:34.622 --> 16:36.081
However...

16:36.249 --> 16:39.835
...not even the richest,
most ridiculous settlement I ever bring in...

16:40.003 --> 16:42.796
...is gonna be as satisfying
as watching those two hyenas...

16:42.964 --> 16:46.466
...across the street
get what's coming to them.

16:50.889 --> 16:52.139
Oh, dear.

16:54.934 --> 16:58.979
You know I'm a fool for those, um,
German-type convertibles.

17:00.732 --> 17:02.774
Come on, lover boy, let's get to court.

17:02.942 --> 17:05.861
Lucien thinks the two hyenas
just might get off.

17:06.029 --> 17:07.613
You saw Lucien?

17:07.780 --> 17:09.406
When? Where?

17:09.574 --> 17:10.656
How is he?

17:10.825 --> 17:12.701
Has he been eating any better?

17:15.579 --> 17:16.997
Just curious.

17:17.165 --> 17:19.499
Um, Miss Ethel...

17:19.666 --> 17:23.878
...refresh my recollection, how long
were you and Lucien together for exactly?

17:24.047 --> 17:25.255
We were never together.

17:25.423 --> 17:27.507
I was his secretary for 20 years.

17:27.675 --> 17:29.468
Come on, old girl.

17:29.636 --> 17:32.137
- You can tell us, you know.
- He was your boyfriend.

17:32.305 --> 17:36.225
I am an upstanding, God-fearing,
respectable Southern woman...

17:36.392 --> 17:40.520
...with unimpeachable morals
who has been happily married for 27 years.

17:40.688 --> 17:44.608
And I have never had
or ever will have any boyfriend.

17:44.776 --> 17:46.276
And if I did...

17:46.444 --> 17:51.531
...it certainly would not be
that old pickled scoundrel Lucien Wilbanks.

17:55.912 --> 17:58.622
She did him. Oh, yeah, a lot.

18:05.380 --> 18:07.673
All right, Billy Ray, step on back.

18:08.466 --> 18:10.759
Come on out. Willard.

18:13.680 --> 18:15.681
All right, boys, today's your big day.

18:15.848 --> 18:17.724
We're gonna take a trip
to the courthouse.

18:17.892 --> 18:19.559
The judge is gonna set your bail.

18:19.727 --> 18:22.521
Then we're gonna come back here,
all nice and peaceful-like.

18:22.689 --> 18:27.567
I get any trouble out of you,
I'm going to integrate this jail.

19:53.946 --> 19:57.366
Mama, Daddy's home!
Daddy's home!

19:58.034 --> 20:00.827
Hannah girl, let's go inside for a minute.

20:00.995 --> 20:03.538
Give Daddy some time to himself.

20:03.706 --> 20:07.292
- Let's-- Let's find a book, okay?
- I wanna see Daddy.

20:07.460 --> 20:08.919
Honey?

20:38.408 --> 20:43.036
Jake? Jake? Are you hurt?
Jake, what happened to you?

20:43.204 --> 20:46.039
Jake, honey, are you okay?
What happened to you?

20:46.207 --> 20:49.501
What is this? What is going on with you?
What happened?

20:49.669 --> 20:51.545
Jake, baby.

20:52.547 --> 20:54.756
What happened?

21:27.915 --> 21:30.041
Okay, okay.

21:46.142 --> 21:47.184
See you, Gwen.

22:01.282 --> 22:03.158
Is the sheriff gonna make a statement?

22:03.326 --> 22:05.118
He might, he might not. I don't know.

22:05.286 --> 22:07.913
- Is it first-degree murder?
- I'm not sure yet.

22:08.080 --> 22:10.081
What happened?
Can you tell us something?

22:10.249 --> 22:13.460
- Sheriff, will you give us a statement.
- I got no comment. No comment.

22:13.628 --> 22:16.588
Hey. Hey, Jake.
Hey, Jake, Carl Lee said you'd be coming.

22:16.756 --> 22:19.049
- Sir, are you an attorney?
- Are you an attorney?

22:19.217 --> 22:22.594
Now, I'll make a statement.
I want y'all to get these vans out of here.

22:22.762 --> 22:25.013
Sir, we've gotta get something
for our newscast.

22:44.825 --> 22:46.618
Didn't think I'd do it, did you?

22:50.373 --> 22:52.207
How you holding up?

22:56.462 --> 22:59.965
I ain't had nothing against them boys
till they messed with my baby.

23:00.883 --> 23:05.095
And I feel sorry for their mamas
and their daddies, but...

23:05.805 --> 23:07.764
...I ain't sorry for what I done.

23:11.018 --> 23:12.143
How's Looney?

23:14.981 --> 23:16.773
You blew his knee right off his leg.

23:17.650 --> 23:19.985
Doctors are still with him.

23:23.948 --> 23:25.448
What's gonna happen to me now?

23:26.951 --> 23:29.244
There's gonna be a preliminary hearing.

23:29.412 --> 23:31.705
Probably tomorrow.

23:32.164 --> 23:34.332
After that, Buckley will push
for a fast trial.

23:35.334 --> 23:36.459
Who's Buckley?

23:36.627 --> 23:38.128
Rufus Buckley.

23:38.296 --> 23:39.337
District attorney.

23:39.505 --> 23:43.508
He's mean, he's ambitious, and he's
gonna eat this up because of the publicity.

23:43.676 --> 23:45.468
But you've done beat him, ain't you?

23:45.970 --> 23:47.637
Yeah.

23:48.014 --> 23:49.639
Not in a murder case.

23:53.519 --> 23:54.978
Think I can win?

23:55.855 --> 23:58.231
All depends on the jury, Carl Lee.

23:59.358 --> 24:01.234
Pick the right jury, and you walk.

24:02.695 --> 24:04.696
DA picks the jury...

24:04.864 --> 24:06.156
...and you get the gas.

24:09.702 --> 24:11.328
Well, how much--?

24:11.495 --> 24:13.496
How much a case like this cost?

24:16.542 --> 24:17.917
Probably 50 grand.

24:20.171 --> 24:23.131
I can pay maybe 10.

24:29.972 --> 24:35.060
Well, not a lot of white lawyers
would've took my brother Lester's case.

24:35.561 --> 24:38.063
You did and got him off.

24:38.898 --> 24:44.486
I figure there's a lot of people out there
tired of all the raping and killing.

24:44.654 --> 24:48.615
They'd be sympathetic to a man
who took the law into his own hands...

24:48.783 --> 24:50.492
...even if he is black.

24:57.750 --> 25:01.670
You said you'd help me out
if I was in a jam, Jake.

25:02.088 --> 25:04.714
Well, I'm in one now.

25:05.925 --> 25:07.050
What you say?

25:09.679 --> 25:12.722
- What can you tell us, sheriff?
- Can you tell us what happened?

25:12.890 --> 25:15.558
- Are you with the police department?
- No, I am a lawyer.

25:15.726 --> 25:17.519
Are you Carl Lee Hailey's attorney?

25:18.479 --> 25:20.939
Sir, are you Mr. Hailey's attorney?

25:21.107 --> 25:22.273
Yes, I am.

25:22.441 --> 25:24.693
- What's your name, sir?
- Brigance. Jake Brigance.

25:24.860 --> 25:26.194
That's with one G.

25:33.828 --> 25:35.286
Hailey's hired an attorney.

25:35.996 --> 25:37.038
Jake Brigance.

25:40.000 --> 25:43.002
And today ain't even my birthday.

25:43.170 --> 25:46.548
Brigance couldn't tie his own tie
without that old drunk Wilbanks.

25:46.716 --> 25:48.675
Telling the press
he never lost a murder case.

25:48.843 --> 25:50.969
Well, he's never tried one against me,
has he?

25:51.137 --> 25:53.638
- What time's the preliminary?
- Tomorrow at 3.

25:53.806 --> 25:55.598
Judge Omar Noose presiding.

25:56.225 --> 25:58.643
Oh, I was wrong. It is my birthday.

25:59.019 --> 26:02.605
All right. First things first,
Brigance will file for a change of venue.

26:02.773 --> 26:05.817
- Guy would be a fool if he didn't.
- Why's that?

26:06.318 --> 26:07.444
Why?

26:07.611 --> 26:09.946
Should we tell our young,
uninformed law clerk...

26:10.114 --> 26:12.282
...the reality of jurisprudence
in this county?

26:12.450 --> 26:16.578
Evelyn, get me the state file
on race statistics.

26:16.746 --> 26:18.371
You see, Taylor, it's quite simple.

26:18.539 --> 26:21.624
This county's 26-, 30-percent black,
give or take.

26:21.792 --> 26:25.920
Almost every other county is 40-, 45-,
in some cases 70-percent black.

26:26.088 --> 26:28.214
Blacks are more sympathetic
to other blacks.

26:28.382 --> 26:31.468
If he gets it moved, he has
a greater chance of color in the jury.

26:31.635 --> 26:32.719
We know what that means.

26:32.887 --> 26:36.055
But if the trial stays here,
it's an all-white jury for sure.

26:36.223 --> 26:37.849
Now, Taylor, this is for you...

26:38.350 --> 26:40.894
...to integrate your brain with
before 3:00 tomorrow.

26:41.061 --> 26:43.396
- Yes.
- He means without blacks on the jury...

26:43.564 --> 26:45.565
...Hailey hasn't got a chance in hell.

26:45.733 --> 26:48.860
- All right, Noose is up for re-elect?
- Yeah, November.

26:49.028 --> 26:51.112
Reach out to our friends
in the legislature.

26:51.280 --> 26:54.908
Have them call on Noose. We're gonna
help him decide to keep this case in Canton.

26:55.075 --> 26:58.912
Also, send a case of whatever it is
he's drinking these days to Lucien Wilbanks.

26:59.079 --> 27:02.582
- I believe that's Dewars.
- Keep that old drunk on the sidelines.

27:02.750 --> 27:03.833
Yeah, get me Sam.

27:04.001 --> 27:05.752
And, gentlemen?

27:07.046 --> 27:10.256
No mistakes.
This is the one we've been waiting for.

27:11.050 --> 27:13.885
Justifiable homicide will never hold up.

27:14.053 --> 27:16.679
Then my only chance
is to find a shrink who'll testify...

27:16.847 --> 27:19.265
...Carl Lee was insane
at the time of the murders.

27:19.558 --> 27:23.728
Well, I might know a man
who owes me a favor.

27:24.396 --> 27:27.982
