- This is really good for Carl Lee.

46:12.732 --> 46:14.358
I'll be right back.

46:15.735 --> 46:17.486
Thank y'all for coming.

46:22.367 --> 46:25.535
I guess we'll have to read about it
in the papers.

47:22.677 --> 47:23.885
Praise Jesus!

47:39.610 --> 47:42.154
- Reverend Agee?
- Yes.

47:42.321 --> 47:43.822
I'm Isaiah Street.

47:43.990 --> 47:46.616
Well, it's an honor to meet you,
Reverend.

47:46.784 --> 47:48.869
I saw you march with Dr. King.

47:49.037 --> 47:55.042
Well, well. The struggle continues today
here in Canton.

47:55.626 --> 47:57.919
Carl Lee Hailey's on trial
because he's black.

47:58.087 --> 47:59.379
No other reason.

48:00.631 --> 48:03.967
- These people are with the NAACP.
- Oh?

48:04.385 --> 48:06.386
- Reverend Agee.
- How do you do?

48:06.554 --> 48:07.637
How do you do?

48:07.972 --> 48:14.311
Reverend Agee, the black community's
concerned that Mr. Hailey's attorney...

48:14.479 --> 48:17.355
...is not sensitive to the needs
of the movement.

48:18.316 --> 48:23.695
The NAACP wishes to provide him
with a new lawyer.

48:25.823 --> 48:30.243
We need to raise funds
to support Carl Lee Hailey.

48:31.329 --> 48:34.331
I don't know, Reverend.
Time's awfully tight here.

48:36.334 --> 48:40.545
Obviously, we would expect you
to take...

48:40.713 --> 48:44.716
...a modest administration fee
for your troubles.

49:10.868 --> 49:17.332
Your loyalty has been forged
in a baptism of fire.

49:18.459 --> 49:22.879
Rise, knights of the Ku Klux Klan...

49:23.506 --> 49:28.176
...and let your brethren never regret...

49:29.220 --> 49:34.391
...they believed you worthy of fellowship.

49:39.730 --> 49:41.857
Welcome to the Klan.

49:53.828 --> 49:55.620
I need to talk to Jake Brigance.

49:55.788 --> 49:58.081
He's not in. May I ask who's calling?

49:58.666 --> 50:01.585
Uh, well--

50:01.794 --> 50:02.836
Mickey Mouse.

50:03.296 --> 50:05.213
- Who?
- Mickey Mouse.

50:06.007 --> 50:08.091
Get out right now.

50:08.259 --> 50:09.259
Who is this?

50:09.427 --> 50:12.179
Get your daughter
out of the house right now.

50:13.347 --> 50:14.723
Mommy!

50:14.891 --> 50:16.933
- Hannah?
- Mommy!

50:17.101 --> 50:20.520
Hannah? What is it? Oh, my God!

50:20.688 --> 50:22.981
Max! Max, come on!

50:23.149 --> 50:24.524
Fire! Aah!

50:32.533 --> 50:35.869
It's a good thing Hastings
was nearby and got here fast.

50:36.037 --> 50:38.455
The whole place could've burned down.

50:38.623 --> 50:41.208
- Yeah, I appreciate it.
- Take care, man.

50:41.375 --> 50:43.335
See you in the morning.

50:49.800 --> 50:51.801
She asleep, baby?

50:53.137 --> 50:56.389
The Ku Klux Klan
is burning crosses on our lawn, Jake.

50:56.557 --> 50:59.643
Baby, there's been
no Klan around here for years, okay?

50:59.810 --> 51:03.647
This is just a couple of dorks with too much
time on their hands and too many beers.

51:08.194 --> 51:10.445
- I'm sorry.
- About what?

51:11.989 --> 51:15.617
That you weren't home when someone
practically burned our house down?

51:15.785 --> 51:18.411
That you missed supper
and didn't even bother to call?

51:18.579 --> 51:21.665
That lately you've become more
interested in getting on the news...

51:21.832 --> 51:23.708
...than what's going on with your family?

51:23.876 --> 51:27.712
Or that Hannah comes home bawling
because of kids calling her a nigger-lover?

51:27.880 --> 51:30.966
What exactly are you sorry about, Jake?

51:39.350 --> 51:41.393
Remember the other night?

51:43.104 --> 51:45.647
I told you Carl Lee came by the office?

51:45.815 --> 51:48.191
Remember what we talked about then?

51:48.651 --> 51:50.652
About me calling Ozzie?

51:53.739 --> 51:56.449
You never called him, did you?

51:57.451 --> 51:58.910
You never called Sheriff Walls?

51:59.912 --> 52:01.705
I didn't call him, baby.

52:02.915 --> 52:06.751
Lord have mercy, Jake,
you had a responsibility.

52:06.919 --> 52:08.878
Carl Lee chose you.

52:09.046 --> 52:12.215
He told you what he was thinking.

52:12.383 --> 52:14.801
He told me what he was thinking,
but I didn't know--

52:14.969 --> 52:19.264
Jake Tyler Brigance,
we agreed, you were gonna call the sheriff.

52:19.432 --> 52:21.850
Now look at everything
that has happened.

52:22.560 --> 52:26.396
I am sorry to tell you this, darling,
but those two boys are in the ground...

52:26.564 --> 52:29.566
...and you were in a position
to prevent every bit of this.

52:29.734 --> 52:30.984
Mama?

52:32.445 --> 52:33.987
Are you and Daddy fighting?

52:35.531 --> 52:39.242
No, baby. Come here.
Come here, baby. Come here.

52:40.202 --> 52:43.788
Mommy's just upset because
some silly man played a real bad joke, okay?

52:43.956 --> 52:45.915
There's nothing to worry about.

52:46.334 --> 52:49.377
Nothing at all, okay?

52:55.009 --> 52:57.010
What that Memphis doctor say about her?

52:58.262 --> 52:59.888
She's doing good.

53:00.890 --> 53:02.432
Her jaw is healing.

53:02.600 --> 53:06.311
She can't run and jump yet,
but it won't be long.

53:07.605 --> 53:09.272
How about the other?

53:17.323 --> 53:20.158
There was too much damage.

53:21.327 --> 53:23.161
She ain't gonna never have kids.

53:31.629 --> 53:33.963
You know, I think about them two boys.

53:34.131 --> 53:35.715
Dead, buried...

53:35.883 --> 53:38.343
...probably starting to rot.

53:38.969 --> 53:41.805
And I remember them walking in court...

53:41.972 --> 53:43.890
...one proud, the other scared.

53:45.518 --> 53:47.602
I remember how they fell.

53:47.770 --> 53:52.816
One on top of the other, and screaming
and squirming and not going nowhere.

53:54.693 --> 53:57.362
God help me, Gwen, but...

53:59.073 --> 54:01.366
...that's the only thought
gives me comfort.

54:04.703 --> 54:07.789
They took up a collection for us
at church Sunday night.

54:08.541 --> 54:10.875
Some kind of defense fund.

54:11.627 --> 54:14.212
Reverend Agee gave a good service.

54:17.508 --> 54:23.847
We need some money around the house,
Carl Lee, for groceries and bills.

54:24.014 --> 54:25.306
How much you got?

54:27.017 --> 54:28.184
Less than 50.

54:30.187 --> 54:31.646
I'll think of something.

54:35.276 --> 54:39.195
How you think you going to get
some money while you stuck here in jail?

54:39.363 --> 54:40.989
Trust me, Gwen.

54:46.162 --> 54:47.954
I just get scared.

54:49.874 --> 54:51.541
Look here.

54:51.876 --> 54:57.672
Tell me exactly what Reverend Agee said
when he passed around the collection plate.

54:57.840 --> 55:01.050
I don't care.
We are dealing with life and death here.

55:01.218 --> 55:05.180
- I'm gonna have to talk to my supervisor.
- Well, you go talk. Get out of here.

55:05.347 --> 55:08.099
Morning, John.
How are things at the electric company?

55:08.267 --> 55:12.187
The electric company. That is the second
time this week I've had to hold him off.

55:12.354 --> 55:14.189
- How much do we owe?
- Two thousand dollars.

55:14.356 --> 55:17.317
- How much do we have?
- One hundred dollars.

55:17.485 --> 55:20.612
Now, look, this week nothing,
nothing has come in at all. Look.

55:20.779 --> 55:23.698
What about Buck Britt's retainer?
There's 2 grand.

55:23.866 --> 55:27.076
- That check bounced.
- What do you mean, bounced?

55:27.244 --> 55:28.995
It bounced, Jake.

55:29.163 --> 55:31.748
It's been sitting on your desk for a week.

55:31.916 --> 55:33.958
Not that you'd notice.

55:35.669 --> 55:39.172
Since you took this case, you--
You stopped talking to your clients...

55:39.340 --> 55:41.132
...you don't take your calls, you--

55:41.300 --> 55:45.178
You're obsessed. That's what you are.
You're obsessed, Jake.

55:45.679 --> 55:48.765
- Boy, your obsession is going to break us.
- Hey, hey, hey.

55:48.933 --> 55:51.601
What's wrong, girl?
We've been through hard times before.

55:51.769 --> 55:53.686
Oh, not like this, Jake.

55:53.854 --> 55:55.939
Not like this.

55:56.857 --> 55:58.858
We've been getting calls.

55:59.026 --> 56:00.193
At home.

56:00.361 --> 56:01.569
Threats.

56:02.947 --> 56:07.242
You know Bud has survived two strokes.
I don't think he would survive a third.

56:07.409 --> 56:08.618
Why didn't you tell me?

56:10.079 --> 56:11.955
Why, Jake?

56:12.122 --> 56:13.498
Would you drop the case?

56:19.338 --> 56:20.547
Jake Brigance's office.

56:20.714 --> 56:23.299
Until they cut the phones off.

56:24.134 --> 56:25.593
Oh, right.

56:26.345 --> 56:27.554
Okay.

56:27.721 --> 56:30.598
Right. That was Sheriff Walls.

56:30.766 --> 56:32.725
You better get down to that jail.

56:40.150 --> 56:42.318
What's going on here, Carl Lee?

56:42.486 --> 56:44.571
- I'm Isaiah Street.
- Jake Brigance.

56:44.738 --> 56:46.906
Uh-huh. Uh....

56:47.074 --> 56:49.158
- I believe you know Reverend Agee.
- Jake.

56:49.326 --> 56:51.494
- And this is--
- Norman Reinfield.

56:51.662 --> 56:53.913
I've seen your picture in the paper.

56:54.790 --> 56:57.500
I assume these boys carry your briefcase.

56:57.668 --> 57:00.336
Just a small part
of my legal defense team.

57:00.504 --> 57:01.879
Pleasure, Mr. Brigance.

57:02.047 --> 57:03.172
Mm-hm.

57:03.340 --> 57:05.717
If this is a party, boys,
where's the chips and beer?

57:06.176 --> 57:10.388
Otherwise, you being here seems a bit
like illegal client solicitation.

57:10.556 --> 57:12.682
With Carl Lee already
having a lawyer and all.

57:12.850 --> 57:14.601
Well, now, just a minute, Jake.

57:14.768 --> 57:16.769
Carl Lee invited us here.

57:18.981 --> 57:20.857
Mr. Brigance...

57:21.025 --> 57:23.318
...let me be frank.

57:23.485 --> 57:26.863
Mr. Hailey's case
has far-reaching ramifications.

57:27.364 --> 57:29.699
Carl Lee's acquittal
for the killings of two white men...

57:29.867 --> 57:32.201
...would do more
for black people in Mississippi...

57:32.369 --> 57:35.747
...than any event since
we integrated the schools.

57:35.914 --> 57:39.083
His conviction, on the other hand,
will be a slap at us.

57:39.251 --> 57:41.377
A symbol of deep-seated racism.

57:41.545 --> 57:43.796
Perhaps enough to ignite a nation.

57:44.214 --> 57:46.382
See how important this case is?

57:46.550 --> 57:49.093
Enter Mr. Reinfield's death squad, right?

57:49.261 --> 57:53.139
It's an unfortunate nickname,
but apropos.

57:53.307 --> 57:56.726
My lawyers and I handle
only capital-murder cases, Mr. Hailey.

57:56.894 --> 58:00.229
Yeah, and of all your cases, Norman,
how many are supposed to be lost...

58:00.397 --> 58:03.024
- ...so you can martyr the victim?
- Now, Mr. Brigance.

58:03.192 --> 58:08.071
How much a defense like that cost?

58:09.114 --> 58:10.657
Yeah.

58:11.533 --> 58:13.117
Would you say about 100,000?

58:13.285 --> 58:17.330
We are prepared to accept
7000 in litigation expenses.

58:17.498 --> 58:21.250
Well, Carl Lee doesn't have $7000.

58:21.418 --> 58:22.460
Do you, Carl Lee?

58:23.003 --> 58:28.591
The NAACP has raised $5000
for Carl Lee's legal defense fund.

58:28.759 --> 58:31.928
And we raised an additional
$2000 from the local churches.

58:32.096 --> 58:33.763
Let me ask you something, Reverend.

58:34.181 --> 58:37.141
How much of that cash
you offer my wife and kids?

58:37.309 --> 58:41.396
Well, that money is to go to pay
for lawyers' fees and stuff like that.

58:41.563 --> 58:43.690
That ain't what you told the church,
now, is it?

58:44.483 --> 58:46.359
You almost cried when you told them...

58:46.527 --> 58:50.738
...how my family might starve if they
didn't donate all they could, didn't you?

58:51.448 --> 58:54.158
Well, the money is for you
and your family, Carl Lee...

58:54.326 --> 58:57.286
...but we thought it'd be better spent
on your legal defense.

58:57.454 --> 59:00.123
Well, speaking of that defense fund...

59:00.290 --> 59:02.792
...can I use that for any lawyer I want?

59:02.960 --> 59:05.795
Well, it's not that simple, Carl Lee.

59:05.963 --> 59:08.840
Actually, it is that simple, Carl Lee.

59:09.007 --> 59:13.720
Unless the NAACP wants to go on record
as soliciting funds under false pretenses.

59:13.887 --> 59:17.098
Listen, Carl Lee, we raised that money...

59:17.266 --> 59:20.309
...for these men to get you out of here,
not for this cracker to--

59:20.477 --> 59:24.355
Now, hey, hey, hey.
Hold on. Hold on right there, now.

59:24.815 --> 59:28.401
Let me just get this straight here,
Reverend.

59:30.988 --> 59:34.407
If you don't give my wife that cash...

59:34.575 --> 59:38.453
...I'm gonna see to it everybody in this
town knows you're a lying crook.

59:39.121 --> 59:41.664
I'm sure your congregation
will be interested to know...

59:41.832 --> 59:45.042
...Gwen and the kids can't eat
because you want in with the NAACP.

59:45.210 --> 59:48.463
That's right.
By the time I get through with you...

59:48.630 --> 59:52.508
...you won't be able to collect 2 cents
in that collection plate on Sunday.

59:52.676 --> 59:56.846
We'll expect the check for the Hailey family
this afternoon, Reverend Agee.

59:57.806 --> 01:00:01.184
Reverend Street,
I sure do appreciate your fine work...

01:00:01.351 --> 01:00:03.561
...but I'm gonna take my chances
with Jake here.

01:00:05.731 --> 01:00:07.982
Thanks for coming down, Mr. Reinfield.

01:00:08.817 --> 01:00:12.320
Uh, and we'll be expecting that check
for Jake's legal services...

01:00:12.488 --> 01:00:14.489
...around the same time this afternoon.

01:00:18.619 --> 01:00:20.328
Good day, men.

01:00:27.127 --> 01:00:28.878
Go.

01:00:32.382 --> 01:00:33.883
Go.

01:00:34.593 --> 01:00:36.177
Good.

01:00:38.472 --> 01:00:40.556
You set that whole thing up, didn't you?

01:00:40.724 --> 01:00:42.600
Couldn't have did it without you, Jake.

01:00:45.145 --> 01:00:47.021
Make one hell of a team, Carl Lee.

01:00:47.815 --> 01:00:50.900
You out there, Jake. I'm in here.

01:00:51.068 --> 01:00:52.401
We ain't no team.

01:01:17.094 --> 01:01:18.719
There's trouble.

01:01:20.264 --> 01:01:22.098
Oh, lookie there.

01:01:27.354 --> 01:01:29.146
No, here's trouble, Harry Rex.

01:01:37.906 --> 01:01:39.657
Hi. You are...?

01:01:39.825 --> 01:01:41.534
Roark, meet Mr. Harry Rex Vonner...

01:01:41.702 --> 01:01:45.288
...the most effective, connected,
morally compromised lawyer in the country.

01:01:45.455 --> 01:01:48.749
- Oh. Ellen Roark, brilliant law student.
- Do with me as you will.

01:01:48.917 --> 01:01:50.960
- Looking forward to it.
- Okay.

01:01:51.461 --> 01:01:54.297
Um, well,
thought this might interest you.

01:01:54.464 --> 01:01:58.843
In all murder trials, it seems the insanity
plea only makes up 1 percent overall.

01:01:59.011 --> 01:02:01.679
And of the 1 percent of that
that resulted in acquittal...

01:02:01.847 --> 01:02:03.806
...success rested almost wholly on the--

01:02:03.974 --> 01:02:08.352
On the defending psychiatrist regardless of
the quality of the psychological testimony.

01:02:08.520 --> 01:02:10.062
- Yeah.
- Shazam.

01:02:10.230 --> 01:02:11.272
She is brilliant.

01:02:11.440 --> 01:02:13.524
"She." That would be me?

01:02:13.692 --> 01:02:15.985
- Now, who else would she be?
- So she would be me.

01:02:16.153 --> 01:02:18.863
She is saying that
if I take this plea to trial...

01:02:19.031 --> 01:02:22.658
...the verdict is going to hinge on whose
shrink the jury finds more credible.

01:02:23.160 --> 01:02:24.577
She would be correct.

01:02:25.162 --> 01:02:26.579
She would.

01:02:27.289 --> 01:02:29.206
So are you sure you don't need any help?

01:02:29.374 --> 01:02:32.835
I do. I'm hiring. Right now. Me.

01:02:33.337 --> 01:02:37.423
Roark, I am sure that I don't need any help.
Thank you, though.

01:02:37.591 --> 01:02:39.508
Okay.

01:02:39.676 --> 01:02:42.929
I guess that would just have
to be your loss, then, huh?

01:02:44.723 --> 01:02:47.099
Nice to meet you, Morally Compromised.

01:02:47.267 --> 01:02:48.476
Pleasure's all mine.

01:02:48.644 --> 01:02:50.186
She.

01:02:53.649 --> 01:02:57.109
Got to love the Lord
for making things like that.

01:02:57.277 --> 01:02:59.862
Sure you don't wanna at least
take a peak at her rÃ©sumÃ©?

01:03:00.030 --> 01:03:02.323
Not like you couldn't use the help.

01:03:02.491 --> 01:03:06.535
No, I don't want to look at her rÃ©sumÃ©,
Harry Rex, because I have you.

01:03:06.703 --> 01:03:08.788
- You do?
- Yeah, buddy.

01:03:08.956 --> 01:03:12.333
This is your chance to put aside
your shady sources, back-alley deals...

01:03:12.501 --> 01:03:16.045
...your greedy divorcÃ©es,
and do some real law for a change.

01:03:17.839 --> 01:03:19.590
Mr. Vonner, in short...

01:03:19.758 --> 01:03:23.386
...you now have the opportunity
to work on a case that matters.

01:03:24.221 --> 01:03:25.596
Let me get this straight.

01:03:25.764 --> 01:03:30.393
You want me to put aside my empty,
soulless, shady...

01:03:30.560 --> 01:03:33.187
...astonishingly lucrative,
divorcÃ©e practice...

01:03:33.355 --> 01:03:37.400
...come work with you on an unwinnable,
bleeding-heart, lose-all-my-friends...

01:03:37.567 --> 01:03:40.069
...straight-to-the-gas-chamber case
because it matters?

01:03:40.237 --> 01:03:41.570
That is a novel idea, I know.

01:03:41.738 --> 01:03:43.990
No way, never,
presumptuous little shit.

01:03:46.743 --> 01:03:48.077
Good night, y'all.

01:03:53.000 --> 01:03:55.209
- Hello?
- I need the sheriff.

01:03:55.377 --> 01:03:58.713
- He's sleeping now.
- Well, get him up.

01:03:58.880 --> 01:04:02.591
- Who is this?
- Someone's gonna die tonight.

01:04:25.198 --> 01:04:27.491
- Unh!
- I got him!

01:04:28.326 --> 01:04:30.619
- Get his ass, Ozzie!
- What's in the case?

01:04:40.839 --> 01:04:43.090
- This thing's ticking.
- What's in the case?

01:04:43.300 --> 01:04:45.593
I ain't saying, nigger.

01:04:49.598 --> 01:04:51.682
- Family out of the house?
- Yeah.

01:04:53.518 --> 01:04:54.769
It's locked.

01:04:59.691 --> 01:05:00.983
Now I want you to open that.

01:05:13.830 --> 01:05:14.872
Oh, man....

01:05:17.250 --> 01:05:18.292
Defuse it.

01:05:18.835 --> 01:05:23.339
I'm gonna take you
and this nigger-lover to hell with--

01:05:24.508 --> 01:05:27.676
Ain't nothing more dangerous
in this world than a fool with a cause.

01:05:27.844 --> 01:05:30.763
Lay that thing back down there.
Let's get the hell out of here.

01:05:30.931 --> 01:05:33.182
Carla loves this house.

01:05:52.369 --> 01:05:55.037
- How you doing, Stan?
- Hey, how you doing?

01:05:55.956 --> 01:05:56.997
Come here, girl.

01:05:58.208 --> 01:06:00.084
Mwah.

01:06:00.836 --> 01:06:03.212
Daddy, are you coming to Grandpa's too?

01:06:03.380 --> 01:06:06.382
Mm-mm. Not this time, baby.
Daddy's gotta stay here and work.

01:06:06.550 --> 01:06:08.467
You and your mama
have a good time, okay?

01:06:08.635 --> 01:06:11.095
- All right.
- All right. You be good.

01:06:11.429 --> 01:06:12.763
Go get your stuff down there.

01:06:14.015 --> 01:06:16.308
You said you'd withdraw
if it got too dangerous.

01:06:16.476 --> 01:06:17.560
I know.

01:06:17.727 --> 01:06:20.271
But I can't quit now, you know that.

01:06:20.814 --> 01:06:24.441
Carl Lee Hailey's facing the gas chamber,
baby. The man is counting on me.

01:06:25.485 --> 01:06:27.695
I understand that, Jake.

01:06:27.863 --> 01:06:30.364
I want you to remember
that we're counting on you too.

01:06:30.532 --> 01:06:32.867
What if something happens to you?

01:06:33.034 --> 01:06:35.911
Nothing's gonna happen to me, baby.
Come here.

01:06:36.371 --> 01:06:38.080
Give me a hug? Hmm?

01:06:38.790 --> 01:06:40.291
Everything's gonna be all right.

01:06:40.458 --> 01:06:43.169
I'm gonna be fine,
you're gonna be fine. Okay?

