You're goddamn right I did.

01:25:05.479 --> 01:25:07.188
I guess I helped killed them.

01:25:11.151 --> 01:25:13.695
So tomorrow, when we get in court...

01:25:15.531 --> 01:25:18.157
...it's not just Carl Lee
I'm trying to get off.

01:25:37.052 --> 01:25:38.303
Burn in hell, Brigance!

01:25:51.734 --> 01:25:53.735
Good job.

01:25:56.613 --> 01:25:59.449
- Nice place--
- How is it you'll drive an hour and half...

01:25:59.616 --> 01:26:03.661
...outside of town to take me to dinner,
but you have no problem...

01:26:03.829 --> 01:26:06.247
...walking me into my motel room?

01:26:06.415 --> 01:26:08.416
Well, with everything that's going on...

01:26:08.584 --> 01:26:10.918
...I don't think we can be too careful.

01:26:11.086 --> 01:26:13.629
Just wanna make sure
it's all safe in here.

01:26:13.797 --> 01:26:15.340
I'm not scared.

01:26:15.507 --> 01:26:18.509
- Oh, yes, I am.
- Of what?

01:26:19.053 --> 01:26:21.387
Of what's going to happen tomorrow.

01:26:21.722 --> 01:26:24.891
All the other cases I've worked on
have only been paper defendants.

01:26:25.059 --> 01:26:29.520
It's just I never knew the towns,
and I never touched the lives or anything.

01:26:29.688 --> 01:26:31.814
So I don't know what it's like.

01:26:38.113 --> 01:26:40.114
Tomorrow morning...

01:26:40.282 --> 01:26:43.868
...Buckley will try to kill Carl Lee Hailey.

01:26:44.453 --> 01:26:46.871
Now, it's on us to stop him.

01:26:47.039 --> 01:26:48.790
Mm-hm.

01:26:49.583 --> 01:26:51.626
So tonight,
go over the battle in your mind.

01:26:51.794 --> 01:26:54.796
Argument, rebuttal,
examination and cross. All of it.

01:26:55.005 --> 01:26:56.172
Mm-hm.

01:26:56.673 --> 01:26:58.800
- Remember something.
- Hmm.

01:26:59.760 --> 01:27:03.471
- You are one of the good guys.
- Okay.

01:27:03.972 --> 01:27:07.642
- And good guy has the spicy on her lip.
- Spicy.

01:27:07.810 --> 01:27:10.395
But still one of the good guys.

01:27:23.450 --> 01:27:25.410
I'm going home.

01:27:25.828 --> 01:27:29.580
Lock the door behind me, Roark.
I'll see you in the morning.

01:27:43.137 --> 01:27:45.179
It's gonna blow, sheriff. It's gonna blow.

01:27:49.017 --> 01:27:51.310
Oz is right over there!

01:27:55.941 --> 01:27:58.109
Wait. Wait. Hold it, Jake. Hold it, Jake.

01:27:58.277 --> 01:27:59.485
- My dog's in there.
- Jake--

01:27:59.653 --> 01:28:01.112
My dog's in there!

01:28:01.280 --> 01:28:02.321
Max!

01:28:02.489 --> 01:28:04.532
Come on. Come on.

01:28:04.700 --> 01:28:06.534
Max!

01:28:08.620 --> 01:28:10.246
Max!

01:28:16.044 --> 01:28:17.879
It's too late.

01:28:38.484 --> 01:28:40.818
Move, move, move.

01:29:18.607 --> 01:29:20.191
Hey, buddy.

01:29:21.318 --> 01:29:22.652
Seen my dog?

01:29:23.111 --> 01:29:24.570
Looking for my dog.

01:29:24.738 --> 01:29:28.699
Max, come here, boy! Let's go!
Come on, Max!

01:29:30.452 --> 01:29:36.332
I booked you on the 9:15 to Gulfport.
Economy, of course.

01:29:36.625 --> 01:29:38.334
Go see your wife and daughter, Jake.

01:29:40.587 --> 01:29:43.005
What'd you do that for, Harry Rex?

01:29:43.215 --> 01:29:45.132
We got trial in less than three hours.

01:29:45.467 --> 01:29:46.509
Oh, come on.

01:29:46.677 --> 01:29:49.053
Noose would give you a continuance
in a flash.

01:29:49.221 --> 01:29:53.182
NAACP boys be down here before lunch.
Drooling.

01:29:53.934 --> 01:29:56.978
Max, let's go, boy! Come on!

01:29:57.854 --> 01:29:59.689
Jake, listen to me.

01:30:00.232 --> 01:30:03.568
Your marriage is on the rocks,
you're about to have an affair.

01:30:03.735 --> 01:30:07.238
Your career's in ruins if you're lucky,
and if you're not, you're dead.

01:30:08.782 --> 01:30:10.283
Don't get me wrong, my friend.

01:30:11.243 --> 01:30:14.161
What you've put into this case,
you even inspired me, and I'm--

01:30:14.329 --> 01:30:16.372
I'm uninspirable.

01:30:16.540 --> 01:30:18.249
Do everyone a favor, though.

01:30:18.417 --> 01:30:20.501
Drop the case.

01:30:23.839 --> 01:30:26.173
No, I can't.

01:30:26.800 --> 01:30:29.343
I won't. I'm not gonna quit.

01:30:30.304 --> 01:30:32.763
I quit now, and all this is for nothing. No.

01:30:36.351 --> 01:30:39.103
Max, come on now.
Max, where are you? Come on, Max!

01:30:39.271 --> 01:30:41.647
Max is dead, and you're next.

01:30:42.733 --> 01:30:44.609
Walk away.

01:30:54.369 --> 01:30:56.996
Max. Come here, boy.

01:30:57.873 --> 01:30:59.790
Come here. Come here, boy. Ha-ha-ha.

01:31:00.000 --> 01:31:01.500
Come here. Come here.

01:31:01.668 --> 01:31:03.878
Who's got the goods, huh? Huh?

01:31:06.423 --> 01:31:09.050
Pretrial strategy at my office
in less than two hours...

01:31:09.217 --> 01:31:11.886
...and I expect to see your ass there.

01:31:12.262 --> 01:31:15.181
Free Carl Lee!
Free Carl Lee! Free Carl Lee!

01:31:15.349 --> 01:31:18.684
Free Carl Lee! Free Carl Lee!
Free Carl Lee!

01:31:26.652 --> 01:31:28.653
Fry Carl Lee.

01:31:30.030 --> 01:31:31.280
Free Carl Lee!

01:31:32.991 --> 01:31:35.368
Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee!

01:31:35.535 --> 01:31:36.744
Free Carl Lee!

01:31:39.665 --> 01:31:41.999
Free Carl Lee! Free Carl Lee!

01:31:46.046 --> 01:31:49.674
Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee!

01:31:49.841 --> 01:31:54.303
Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee! Fry Carl Lee!

01:32:01.520 --> 01:32:04.897
Now, Mr. Buckley, you may begin.

01:32:05.065 --> 01:32:06.941
Thank you, Your Honor.

01:32:09.778 --> 01:32:12.405
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

01:32:14.324 --> 01:32:18.994
You are Cora Mae Cobb, the mother of
Billy Ray Cobb the deceased, are you not?

01:32:19.162 --> 01:32:20.621
Yes, sir.

01:32:20.789 --> 01:32:23.207
And where were you
when your son was murdered?

01:32:23.500 --> 01:32:26.711
I was right outside that door right there.

01:32:26.878 --> 01:32:29.672
Me and Freddie was waiting
for his hearing.

01:32:30.173 --> 01:32:32.174
He was walking up the stairs...

01:32:32.342 --> 01:32:34.135
...in handcuffs.

01:32:34.428 --> 01:32:38.013
Can you tell us how old your son was
at the time of his death?

01:32:39.391 --> 01:32:40.474
Twenty-three.

01:32:42.352 --> 01:32:44.520
You say your son was 23 when he died?

01:32:44.938 --> 01:32:45.980
Yes.

01:32:46.148 --> 01:32:49.066
In those 23 years, Mrs. Cobb...

01:32:49.234 --> 01:32:51.360
...how many other children
did your son kidnap?

01:32:51.528 --> 01:32:53.320
Objection, Your Honor! Objection!

01:32:53.488 --> 01:32:57.116
Sustained. You--
You are out of order, Mr. Brigance.

01:32:57.284 --> 01:32:59.952
- Withdraw the question.
- The jury will disregard...

01:33:00.120 --> 01:33:02.288
...the last question from Mr. Brigance.

01:33:03.165 --> 01:33:06.584
Mrs. Cobb, in your son's 23 years...

01:33:06.752 --> 01:33:08.794
...how many other children did he rape?

01:33:08.962 --> 01:33:11.589
Mr. Brigance. In my chambers.

01:33:12.674 --> 01:33:14.008
Court will recess for lunch.

01:33:16.845 --> 01:33:19.430
I don't get it.
Why is he antagonizing the judge?

01:33:19.598 --> 01:33:21.849
He should've known
Noose'd pull him into chambers.

01:33:22.017 --> 01:33:26.270
Of course he knew. Jake got to draw first
blood and he knows that's more important.

01:33:27.397 --> 01:33:29.273
- Hello, Harry.
- Hi, Rufie.

01:33:29.441 --> 01:33:33.319
- Sweetheart, come play on a winning team.
- How's that impotence thing, Rufus?

01:33:36.740 --> 01:33:39.533
You're not being paid
for the work you're doing, are you?

01:33:39.701 --> 01:33:40.785
No, sir.

01:33:42.204 --> 01:33:44.622
Well, I guess Jake's paying you
in other ways, then, isn't he?

01:33:46.792 --> 01:33:47.875
Impotence?

01:33:48.043 --> 01:33:49.668
Yep. Girls talk.

01:33:49.836 --> 01:33:54.673
Sheriff, if you would,
will you please identify this weapon?

01:33:54.841 --> 01:33:56.425
It's the weapon found
at the scene.

01:33:57.135 --> 01:34:01.138
And were you able to identify
any of the fingerprints found on this gun?

01:34:01.389 --> 01:34:04.600
Yes. The prints on the gun
matched those of Carl Lee Hailey.

01:34:04.768 --> 01:34:06.227
You're sure?

01:34:06.728 --> 01:34:08.062
Yes.

01:34:08.230 --> 01:34:12.441
Your Honor, I'd like to enter this
into evidence as Exhibit S18.

01:34:12.609 --> 01:34:14.860
We have no further use of this witness.

01:34:18.990 --> 01:34:20.991
Sheriff Walls.

01:34:22.369 --> 01:34:24.286
Did you arrest Cobb and Willard?

01:34:24.454 --> 01:34:25.955
Yes, I did.

01:34:26.122 --> 01:34:28.165
I arrested them for the rape...

01:34:28.333 --> 01:34:32.253
...and attempted murder
of 10-year-old Tonya Hailey.

01:34:32.420 --> 01:34:34.046
And is it true that Pete Willard...

01:34:34.214 --> 01:34:36.006
...signed a written confession...

01:34:36.174 --> 01:34:39.844
...saying that he and Billy Ray Cobb
did rape Tonya Hailey?

01:34:40.011 --> 01:34:42.930
Objection. That's inadmissible,
and Mr. Brigance knows it.

01:34:43.098 --> 01:34:45.933
Mr. Brigance,
I've spoken to you before.

01:34:46.101 --> 01:34:48.936
We are not trying the rape
of Miss Hailey today...

01:34:49.104 --> 01:34:53.774
...but the murder of two young men,
and if you continue in this performance...

01:34:54.609 --> 01:34:56.235
...I'll hold you in contempt.

01:34:56.486 --> 01:34:57.987
Now, is that understood?

01:34:58.989 --> 01:35:00.531
Yes, sir.

01:35:01.867 --> 01:35:04.118
I have no further questions,
Your Honor.

01:35:04.286 --> 01:35:05.953
Yes.

01:35:07.122 --> 01:35:09.081
You say something, sheriff?

01:35:10.959 --> 01:35:14.128
- Yes, he did sign a confession.
- Objection, Your Honor!

01:35:14.546 --> 01:35:19.550
Jurors, you will disregard
the last remark of Sheriff Walls.

01:35:19.718 --> 01:35:23.679
Court is adjourned
till tomorrow morning 9:00.

01:35:44.659 --> 01:35:46.869
I'm taking Bud back to Oxford.

01:35:48.455 --> 01:35:50.748
He always missed Oxford.

01:36:07.641 --> 01:36:10.100
I don't know what to say,
Ethel, I don't know.

01:36:10.268 --> 01:36:12.770
There's nothing you can say.

01:36:14.022 --> 01:36:17.191
I know you didn't want
any of this to happen...

01:36:17.359 --> 01:36:19.276
...but it happened all the same.

01:36:21.196 --> 01:36:24.615
You wagered all our lives on this.

01:36:25.075 --> 01:36:29.703
You just went ahead and did what you
felt you had to do, no matter what the cost.

01:36:32.040 --> 01:36:35.000
Some folks think that's brave.

01:36:35.877 --> 01:36:38.003
Not me, Jake.

01:36:38.922 --> 01:36:40.839
Now, you may win...

01:36:41.466 --> 01:36:44.343
...but I think we've all lost here.

01:36:51.059 --> 01:36:56.897
- Would you help an old lady to her car?
- You don't need any help, Ethel...

01:36:57.065 --> 01:37:01.527
...but it would be my honor
to escort you to your automobile.

01:37:16.001 --> 01:37:17.960
Didn't like that one?

01:37:18.378 --> 01:37:20.337
Buckley is presenting
his shrink tomorrow.

01:37:20.505 --> 01:37:23.632
I can't come up with one way
to bring him down. Not one.

01:37:23.800 --> 01:37:28.053
I keep asking myself, "What would
Jake do? What would my father do?

01:37:28.221 --> 01:37:29.263
What would Lucien do?"

01:37:29.431 --> 01:37:31.724
That's your problem right there.

01:37:31.891 --> 01:37:35.769
What you gotta ask yourself is,
"What would Harry Rex do?"

01:37:35.937 --> 01:37:37.521
What would Harry Rex do?

01:37:37.689 --> 01:37:39.023
Cheat.

01:37:39.190 --> 01:37:40.607
Cheat like crazy.

01:37:45.113 --> 01:37:46.113
Yeah. Yeah, I did.

01:37:46.281 --> 01:37:49.116
I'll bring her around the side.

01:37:51.870 --> 01:37:53.203
Uh-huh.

01:37:53.371 --> 01:37:54.872
- Hey, Cheryl.
- Hi.

01:37:56.666 --> 01:37:58.167
So we gotta talk about it.

01:37:58.752 --> 01:38:00.044
Now, wait a minute.

01:38:00.211 --> 01:38:03.088
The judge said absolutely
not to discuss this case.

01:38:03.256 --> 01:38:05.799
That judge ain't stuck here
away from his wife and kids.

01:38:05.967 --> 01:38:09.845
The sooner we start talking about it,
the sooner we can get home.

01:38:10.013 --> 01:38:12.473
I wanna get out of here
just as much as anybody else.

01:38:12.640 --> 01:38:14.475
Let's get on with it.

01:38:16.478 --> 01:38:17.895
Undecided?

01:38:21.232 --> 01:38:22.733
Four.

01:38:22.901 --> 01:38:24.777
Guilty?

01:38:29.491 --> 01:38:31.325
Seven.

01:38:31.993 --> 01:38:33.035
Not guilty?

01:38:37.665 --> 01:38:40.000
That nigger's dead, y'all.

01:38:58.186 --> 01:39:01.688
I know, I know. Folks in town
just can't get enough of this trial.

01:39:01.856 --> 01:39:06.026
And that's why my editor said I needed
to come down and interview Rodeheaver.

01:39:06.569 --> 01:39:08.946
I'm afraid
Dr. Rodeheaver's in court today.

01:39:09.489 --> 01:39:10.531
Oh.

01:39:11.074 --> 01:39:13.534
If a pretty girl like you
wants to be a reporter...

01:39:13.701 --> 01:39:15.702
...maybe she should do
some better research?

01:39:15.870 --> 01:39:16.912
Yeah. Ha.

01:39:17.080 --> 01:39:20.374
Well, um, you know what?
I don't-- I don't mind waiting...

01:39:20.542 --> 01:39:23.043
...because my paper really wants
this interview...

01:39:23.211 --> 01:39:25.462
...so is he still in Room 369?
I'll just go there.

01:39:25.630 --> 01:39:29.842
No, dear. Wrong again. He's in 128.
But he's gone all day.

01:39:30.009 --> 01:39:31.510
You can't see him today.

01:39:31.678 --> 01:39:35.389
You wanna come back to my office
and we can schedule an appointment?

01:39:35.557 --> 01:39:37.683
You know what?
I'll come back another time...

01:39:37.851 --> 01:39:40.602
...when he's got time to talk,
when things kind of die down.

01:39:40.770 --> 01:39:43.313
- I appreciate it. Thank you.
- You can call me any time.

01:39:43.481 --> 01:39:45.315
Okay. Bye-bye.

01:39:48.570 --> 01:39:52.322
Your Honor,
the state calls Deputy Dwayne Looney.

01:40:28.276 --> 01:40:29.776
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

01:40:29.944 --> 01:40:32.905
Would you please state
your name for the record?

01:40:33.072 --> 01:40:36.283
Deputy Dwayne Powell Looney.

01:40:36.451 --> 01:40:38.243
Thank you, Deputy Looney.

01:40:38.411 --> 01:40:41.038
You were present at the murders
of Billy Ray Cobb...

01:40:41.206 --> 01:40:43.457
...and James Lewis Willard,
were you not?

01:40:43.625 --> 01:40:45.209
Yes, sir. I was.

01:40:45.376 --> 01:40:47.252
If you can remember...

01:40:47.420 --> 01:40:51.632
...describe how you were wounded
for the members of the jury.

01:40:51.799 --> 01:40:55.302
I think bullets bounced off the floor,
caught me in the knee.

01:40:55.470 --> 01:40:57.387
And what happened to your leg?

01:40:58.765 --> 01:41:00.057
Doc cut it off.

01:41:01.392 --> 01:41:06.438
And after the loss of your right leg,
Detective Looney...

01:41:07.398 --> 01:41:09.775
...are you still able
to serve as a police officer?

01:41:11.694 --> 01:41:14.029
I'm able to perform....

01:41:17.659 --> 01:41:21.161
I'm able to perform a number of services.

01:41:21.329 --> 01:41:23.956
Did you get a good look at the man
with the gun?

01:41:24.123 --> 01:41:25.165
No, sir.

01:41:26.167 --> 01:41:31.338
However, Mr. Hailey did personally
apologize for his shooting me.

01:41:33.466 --> 01:41:34.883
Oh.

01:41:36.636 --> 01:41:39.805
So Mr. Hailey admitted shooting you.

01:41:40.390 --> 01:41:41.431
Yes, sir.

01:41:41.599 --> 01:41:43.475
I have no further questions, Your Honor.

01:41:43.643 --> 01:41:45.560
- Mr. Brigance.
- No questions, Your Honor.

01:41:45.728 --> 01:41:47.187
Wait a minute.

01:41:47.355 --> 01:41:49.856
- Uh, Mr. Buckley?
- Yes, Your Honor.

01:41:50.024 --> 01:41:51.400
The state would like to call--

01:41:51.567 --> 01:41:53.527
Give me a moment
to speak with my client.

01:41:53.695 --> 01:41:54.861
Take your time.

01:41:56.823 --> 01:41:59.074
Ask him if he thinks I ought to go to jail.

01:41:59.367 --> 01:42:02.327
Carl Lee, they amputated his leg
because you shot him.

01:42:02.495 --> 01:42:04.288
He's a witness for the prosecution.

01:42:04.455 --> 01:42:06.540
- You're my lawyer, ain't you?
- Yeah.

01:42:07.083 --> 01:42:08.959
Ask him.

01:42:15.258 --> 01:42:19.386
- Your Honor, one question.
- Make up your mind, Mr. Brigance.

01:42:23.641 --> 01:42:24.683
Deputy Looney.

01:42:26.269 --> 01:42:29.396
Do you think Carl Lee
shooting you was intentional?

01:42:29.564 --> 01:42:30.981
No, sir.

01:42:31.149 --> 01:42:32.482
It was an accident.

01:42:36.904 --> 01:42:37.946
Ask him.

01:42:45.038 --> 01:42:47.998
Do you think he should be punished
for shooting you?

01:42:48.791 --> 01:42:50.542
No, sir.

01:42:50.710 --> 01:42:54.338
I hold no ill will toward the man.

01:42:54.756 --> 01:42:56.590
He did what I would've done.

01:42:56.758 --> 01:42:58.675
What do you mean by that,
Deputy Looney?

01:42:58.843 --> 01:43:01.303
I mean I don't blame him
for what he did.

01:43:01.471 --> 01:43:03.305
Those boys raped his little girl.

01:43:03.473 --> 01:43:07.976
Objection, Your Honor. The witness's
opinion on this matter is irrelevant.

01:43:08.144 --> 01:43:13.857
Your Honor, I believe Deputy Looney
has earned the right to speak here today.

01:43:15.401 --> 01:43:16.568
Overruled.

01:43:17.779 --> 01:43:19.404
Continue.

01:43:22.158 --> 01:43:23.367
Go ahead, Dwayne.

01:43:24.577 --> 01:43:26.828
I got a little girl.

01:43:28.706 --> 01:43:31.375
Somebody rapes her, he's a dead dog.

01:43:31.542 --> 01:43:33.752
I'll blow him away just like Carl Lee did.

01:43:33.920 --> 01:43:35.128
Objection, Your Honor!

01:43:35.296 --> 01:43:37.464
Do you think the jury
should convict Carl Lee?

01:43:37.632 --> 01:43:39.925
Don't answer that question, deputy.

01:43:40.093 --> 01:43:42.219
He's a hero. You turn him loose.

01:43:42.387 --> 01:43:44.471
Jury will disregard.

01:43:44.639 --> 01:43:45.889
Turn him loose!

01:43:46.307 --> 01:43:48.558
Your Honor, you silence that witness!

01:43:48.726 --> 01:43:50.727
Turn him loose!

01:43:55.149 --> 01:43:56.274
No!

01:43:58.152 --> 01:44:01.363
People say whatever the hell
they want in this courtroom!

01:44:01.697 --> 01:44:03.240
Quiet!

01:44:05.952 --> 01:44:08.328
Any more of that nonsense...

01:44:08.496 --> 01:44:10.122
...and you're all out of here.

01:44:12.417 --> 01:44:15.252
Now, Mr. Buckley, you may begin.

01:44:15.420 --> 01:44:17.462
Thank you, Your Honor.

01:44:18.089 --> 01:44:22.717
Would you please state your name and
occupation for the members of the jury.

01:44:22.885 --> 01:44:27.139
