02:03:34.160 --> 02:03:36.954
...What's-His-Name
said I'll be out in a couple days...

02:03:37.122 --> 02:03:38.247
...so I'm fine.

02:03:42.335 --> 02:03:43.627
How'd we do?

02:03:45.547 --> 02:03:48.465
Bass turned out to be a felon.

02:03:49.259 --> 02:03:52.970
Carl Lee got trapped on the stand
by Buckley.

02:03:55.849 --> 02:03:58.601
People been terrorized, Roark.

02:03:58.768 --> 02:04:00.519
Beaten.

02:04:02.439 --> 02:04:04.815
Killed. It--

02:04:05.400 --> 02:04:07.151
It's not worth it. It's not.

02:04:09.738 --> 02:04:13.407
It's only not worth it
if Carl Lee goes to the gas chamber.

02:04:16.953 --> 02:04:20.080
Listen, this case is not over
until the summation.

02:04:20.248 --> 02:04:22.291
Remember that.

02:04:22.667 --> 02:04:24.209
Okay?

02:04:25.503 --> 02:04:29.381
And you've got one big fat chance...

02:04:30.300 --> 02:04:31.467
...to reinvent yourself.

02:04:32.344 --> 02:04:37.640
To make that jury see this whole case--
This whole case through your eyes.

02:04:44.397 --> 02:04:45.773
And they're good eyes.

02:04:51.237 --> 02:04:53.530
Now, get out of here, go to work.

02:04:55.659 --> 02:04:57.117
I'll keep in touch with you.

02:04:57.535 --> 02:04:58.869
No, you won't.

02:04:59.037 --> 02:05:00.579
Big liar.

02:05:10.465 --> 02:05:12.925
Win or lose, Roark...

02:05:14.302 --> 02:05:16.178
...we make one hell of a team.

02:05:17.555 --> 02:05:19.682
We might have.

02:05:20.767 --> 02:05:22.726
We really might have.

02:05:27.023 --> 02:05:29.900
You really want to kiss me right now,
don't you?

02:05:31.486 --> 02:05:33.612
Yes, I do.

02:05:55.468 --> 02:05:56.593
Undecided?

02:05:59.222 --> 02:06:00.848
Guilty?

02:06:39.220 --> 02:06:42.014
Hey, Max. Hey.

02:06:49.189 --> 02:06:50.314
Where's Hannah?

02:06:50.482 --> 02:06:53.108
I left her at Mother and Daddy's.

02:06:54.736 --> 02:06:55.903
How did you get here?

02:06:56.529 --> 02:06:57.905
Drove.

02:06:58.531 --> 02:07:00.032
In the storm?

02:07:02.368 --> 02:07:05.704
Got something to say,
it needs to be said in person.

02:07:10.418 --> 02:07:14.004
The truth is, I've been blaming you
for all that's happened.

02:07:16.925 --> 02:07:19.843
But it's not your fault.
You didn't kill those boys.

02:07:25.350 --> 02:07:27.351
You were trying to make things right.

02:07:29.521 --> 02:07:31.563
I know that now.

02:07:37.320 --> 02:07:40.113
I thought you took this case
because you wanted to prove...

02:07:40.281 --> 02:07:42.908
...what a bigtime lawyer you were.

02:07:43.701 --> 02:07:45.786
But I was wrong.

02:07:49.415 --> 02:07:52.251
You took this case because...

02:07:52.418 --> 02:07:54.628
...if those boys...

02:07:57.006 --> 02:08:01.802
...had hurt Hannah
the way that they hurt Tonya...

02:08:01.970 --> 02:08:03.887
...you would've killed them yourself.

02:08:06.933 --> 02:08:08.642
Baby.

02:08:11.062 --> 02:08:13.856
Baby, come here.

02:08:14.023 --> 02:08:15.858
Come here.

02:08:18.319 --> 02:08:20.654
I love you, Jake.

02:08:22.073 --> 02:08:24.449
I thought I was gonna lose you.

02:08:49.100 --> 02:08:51.810
We're gonna lose this case, Carl Lee.

02:08:54.355 --> 02:08:58.483
There are no points of law to argue here.
I wanna cop a plea.

02:09:00.486 --> 02:09:02.404
Maybe Buckley will cop us...

02:09:02.572 --> 02:09:05.949
...a second-degree murder
and we can get you just life in prison.

02:09:07.785 --> 02:09:11.496
Jake, I-- I can't do no life in prison.

02:09:11.664 --> 02:09:14.082
You gotta get me off.
Man, if it was you on trial--

02:09:14.250 --> 02:09:15.918
It's not me.

02:09:16.836 --> 02:09:18.211
We're not the same, Carl Lee.

02:09:21.132 --> 02:09:24.384
The jury has to identify
with the defendant.

02:09:24.552 --> 02:09:26.303
They see you, they see a yard worker.

02:09:26.471 --> 02:09:30.474
They see me, they see an attorney.
I live in town. You live on the hill.

02:09:30.642 --> 02:09:33.685
Oh, you white and I'm black.

02:09:36.147 --> 02:09:37.856
See, Jake?

02:09:38.232 --> 02:09:40.442
You think just like them.

02:09:41.527 --> 02:09:43.904
That's why I picked you.

02:09:44.906 --> 02:09:47.574
You're one of them, don't you see?

02:09:47.742 --> 02:09:50.077
You think you ain't,
because you eat in Claude's...

02:09:50.244 --> 02:09:54.957
...and you're out there trying to get me off
on TV, talking about black and white.

02:09:55.124 --> 02:09:57.084
But the fact is...

02:09:57.251 --> 02:09:59.962
...you're just like all the rest of them.

02:10:00.129 --> 02:10:03.090
When you look at me,
you don't see a man.

02:10:03.257 --> 02:10:05.175
You see a black man.

02:10:06.010 --> 02:10:09.429
Carl Lee, I am your friend.

02:10:09.597 --> 02:10:11.348
We ain't no friends, Jake.

02:10:12.642 --> 02:10:15.644
We're on different sides of the line.

02:10:15.812 --> 02:10:20.232
I ain't never seen you in my part of town.
I bet you don't even know where I live.

02:10:22.026 --> 02:10:25.070
Our daughters, Jake,
they ain't never gonna play together.

02:10:25.238 --> 02:10:27.614
Now, what are you talking about?

02:10:29.867 --> 02:10:33.078
America is a war...

02:10:33.246 --> 02:10:35.539
...and you are on the other side.

02:10:37.291 --> 02:10:40.127
How a black man
ever gonna get a fair trial...

02:10:40.294 --> 02:10:43.296
...with the enemy on the bench
and the jury box?

02:10:43.464 --> 02:10:46.925
My life in white hands.

02:10:47.176 --> 02:10:48.260
You, Jake.

02:10:48.970 --> 02:10:50.887
That's how.

02:10:51.055 --> 02:10:55.267
You my secret weapon
because you're one of the bad guys.

02:10:55.435 --> 02:10:58.311
You don't mean to be, but you are.

02:10:58.479 --> 02:11:00.772
It's how you was raised.

02:11:00.940 --> 02:11:05.277
Nigger, Negro, black, African-American.

02:11:05.445 --> 02:11:07.571
No matter how you see me...

02:11:07.739 --> 02:11:10.449
...you see me as different.

02:11:10.616 --> 02:11:13.952
You see me like that jury sees me.

02:11:14.120 --> 02:11:15.912
You are them.

02:11:16.706 --> 02:11:19.708
Now, throw out your points of law, Jake.

02:11:20.543 --> 02:11:24.796
If you was on that jury...

02:11:24.964 --> 02:11:29.593
...what would it take
to convince you to set me free?

02:11:32.013 --> 02:11:34.973
That's how you'll save my ass.

02:11:35.558 --> 02:11:37.726
That's how you'll save us both.

02:11:42.273 --> 02:11:46.777
Is Carl Lee Hailey insane?

02:11:47.653 --> 02:11:50.072
It's a notion so outrageous...

02:11:50.239 --> 02:11:54.576
...the only witness
the defense could produce to support it...

02:11:54.744 --> 02:11:56.745
...was a convicted felon.

02:11:57.497 --> 02:12:00.123
No. Carl Lee Hailey is not insane.

02:12:00.291 --> 02:12:03.543
This is a man
who is a confessed murderer.

02:12:04.796 --> 02:12:09.633
This is a man who admitted
on this stand...

02:12:09.801 --> 02:12:13.011
...to carrying out the sentences
he believed the alleged rapists...

02:12:13.179 --> 02:12:15.180
...of his daughter deserved.

02:12:15.348 --> 02:12:17.682
He's taken justice out of your hands.

02:12:20.436 --> 02:12:21.770
And put it in his own.

02:12:22.605 --> 02:12:27.275
And with those hands,
he took the lives of two young men.

02:12:30.363 --> 02:12:33.490
We feel terrible
over what happened to his daughter.

02:12:33.991 --> 02:12:35.742
But feeling terrible...

02:12:35.910 --> 02:12:40.288
...and knowing something is wrong
does not give any of us...

02:12:40.790 --> 02:12:42.415
...a right to kill.

02:12:44.043 --> 02:12:46.253
Ladies and gentlemen, your duty is clear.

02:12:49.340 --> 02:12:52.050
All in this courtroom know the truth.

02:12:52.468 --> 02:12:55.512
All in this state know the truth.

02:12:56.430 --> 02:13:01.351
Now you need only find the courage
to speak the words:

02:13:01.727 --> 02:13:05.397
"Carl Lee Hailey is guilty."

02:13:06.399 --> 02:13:09.109
Guilty. Guilty.

02:13:11.404 --> 02:13:13.780
State rests, Your Honor.

02:13:29.589 --> 02:13:33.383
Now, I had a great summation
all worked out...

02:13:33.593 --> 02:13:36.136
...full of some sharp lawyering.

02:13:37.388 --> 02:13:38.722
But I'm not going to read it.

02:13:40.141 --> 02:13:41.808
I'm here to apologize.

02:13:41.976 --> 02:13:45.437
I am young, and I am inexperienced.

02:13:46.063 --> 02:13:51.026
But you cannot
hold Carl Lee Hailey responsible...

02:13:51.485 --> 02:13:53.028
...for my shortcomings.

02:13:54.238 --> 02:13:56.907
But you see,
in all this legal maneuvering...

02:13:57.074 --> 02:13:59.451
...something has gotten lost.

02:13:59.619 --> 02:14:02.329
And that something is the truth.

02:14:06.125 --> 02:14:10.629
Now, it is incumbent upon us lawyers
not to just talk about the truth...

02:14:10.796 --> 02:14:14.549
...but to actually seek it,
to find it, to live it.

02:14:16.260 --> 02:14:17.761
My teacher taught me that.

02:14:20.181 --> 02:14:22.140
Let's take Dr. Bass, for example.

02:14:22.767 --> 02:14:26.144
Obviously, I would've never knowingly
put a convicted felon on the stand.

02:14:26.312 --> 02:14:27.729
I hope you can believe that.

02:14:28.189 --> 02:14:29.648
But what is the truth?

02:14:29.815 --> 02:14:32.734
That-- That he's a disgraced liar?

02:14:32.902 --> 02:14:34.819
What if I told you...

02:14:34.987 --> 02:14:38.657
...that the woman he was accused
of raping was 17, he was 23...

02:14:38.824 --> 02:14:41.701
...that she later became his wife,
bore his child...

02:14:41.869 --> 02:14:43.495
...and is still married to the man?

02:14:43.663 --> 02:14:47.666
Does that make his testimony
more or less true?

02:14:51.963 --> 02:14:53.755
What is it in us that seeks the truth?

02:14:55.341 --> 02:14:57.259
Is it our minds?

02:14:57.885 --> 02:14:59.386
Or is it our hearts?

02:15:03.266 --> 02:15:06.643
I set out to prove a black man
could receive a fair trial in the South...

02:15:06.811 --> 02:15:09.980
...that we are all equal
in the eyes of the law.

02:15:11.691 --> 02:15:13.275
That's not the truth.

02:15:13.442 --> 02:15:15.694
Because the eyes of the law
are human eyes...

02:15:15.861 --> 02:15:19.823
...yours and mine,
and until we can see each other as equals...

02:15:19.991 --> 02:15:22.325
...justice is never going to be
evenhanded.

02:15:22.493 --> 02:15:26.329
It will remain nothing more than
a reflection of our own prejudices.

02:15:26.622 --> 02:15:29.040
So until that day...

02:15:29.208 --> 02:15:32.460
...we have a duty under God
to seek the truth...

02:15:34.338 --> 02:15:36.464
...not with our eyes,
and not with our minds...

02:15:36.632 --> 02:15:40.218
...where fear and hate turn
commonality into prejudice...

02:15:40.386 --> 02:15:42.595
...but with our hearts...

02:15:42.888 --> 02:15:45.223
...where we don't know better.

02:15:49.562 --> 02:15:51.980
I wanna tell you a story.

02:15:53.733 --> 02:15:56.443
And I ask you all to close your eyes...

02:15:58.070 --> 02:16:00.322
...while I tell you this story.

02:16:03.784 --> 02:16:07.662
I want you to listen to me.
I want you to listen to yourselves.

02:16:11.709 --> 02:16:14.627
Go ahead. Close your eyes, please.

02:16:19.800 --> 02:16:22.594
This is a story about a little girl...

02:16:23.512 --> 02:16:27.265
...walking home from the grocery store
one sunny afternoon.

02:16:28.601 --> 02:16:30.685
I want you to picture this little girl.

02:16:34.106 --> 02:16:36.523
Suddenly, a truck races up.

02:16:38.277 --> 02:16:39.861
Two men jump out and grab her.

02:16:42.490 --> 02:16:45.617
Drag her into a nearby field...

02:16:48.495 --> 02:16:49.870
...and they tie her up.

02:16:53.751 --> 02:16:55.752
And they rip her clothes from her body.

02:16:58.589 --> 02:17:00.882
Now they climb on.

02:17:01.759 --> 02:17:03.968
First one, then the other.

02:17:05.971 --> 02:17:07.055
Raping her.

02:17:12.019 --> 02:17:16.981
Shattering everything innocent and pure
with a vicious thrust...

02:17:17.983 --> 02:17:21.361
...in a fog of drunken breath and sweat.

02:17:25.281 --> 02:17:27.200
And when they're done...

02:17:28.326 --> 02:17:31.413
...after they've killed her tiny womb...

02:17:33.582 --> 02:17:36.876
...murdered any chance
for her to bear children...

02:17:37.044 --> 02:17:39.712
...to have life beyond her own...

02:17:43.174 --> 02:17:45.300
...they decide to use her
for target practice.

02:17:48.180 --> 02:17:51.349
So they start throwing
full beer cans at her.

02:17:53.352 --> 02:17:55.687
They throw them so hard...

02:17:56.355 --> 02:17:59.816
...that it tears the flesh
all the way to her bones.

02:18:05.990 --> 02:18:07.615
Then they urinate on her.

02:18:12.370 --> 02:18:13.745
Now comes the hanging.

02:18:18.919 --> 02:18:20.753
They have a rope.

02:18:22.047 --> 02:18:23.882
They tie a noose.

02:18:25.049 --> 02:18:28.386
Imagine the noose coiling
tight around her neck...

02:18:28.929 --> 02:18:31.556
...and a sudden blinding jerk.

02:18:32.641 --> 02:18:35.518
She's pulled into the air
and her feet and legs go kicking....

02:18:35.686 --> 02:18:37.437
They don't find the ground.

02:18:39.607 --> 02:18:41.483
The hanging branch...

02:18:41.650 --> 02:18:43.610
...isn't strong enough.

02:18:45.279 --> 02:18:47.906
It snaps and she falls...

02:18:48.281 --> 02:18:49.616
...back to the earth.

02:18:53.620 --> 02:18:55.621
So they pick her up...

02:18:56.749 --> 02:18:59.083
...throw her in the back of the truck...

02:19:00.920 --> 02:19:04.088
...drive out to Foggy Creek Bridge...

02:19:04.924 --> 02:19:06.299
...pitch her over the edge.

02:19:09.512 --> 02:19:14.389
And she drops some 30 feet
down to the creek bottom below.

02:19:21.898 --> 02:19:23.775
Can you see her?

02:19:27.571 --> 02:19:29.239
Her raped...

02:19:29.406 --> 02:19:31.156
...beaten...

02:19:31.325 --> 02:19:33.535
...broken body...

02:19:36.621 --> 02:19:38.998
...soaked in their urine...

02:19:39.625 --> 02:19:41.959
...soaked in their semen...

02:19:43.963 --> 02:19:45.797
...soaked in her blood.

02:19:46.799 --> 02:19:48.675
Left to die.

02:19:51.679 --> 02:19:53.555
Can you see her?

02:19:57.560 --> 02:19:59.811
I want you to picture...

02:20:01.605 --> 02:20:03.523
...that little girl.

02:20:22.251 --> 02:20:24.085
Now imagine she's white.

02:20:46.233 --> 02:20:48.026
The defense rests, Your Honor.

02:21:18.390 --> 02:21:19.974
Innocent! He's innocent!

02:21:20.142 --> 02:21:21.726
Innocent! He's innocent!

02:21:21.894 --> 02:21:23.061
Hailey's innocent!

02:21:30.736 --> 02:21:31.861
He's innocent!

02:21:42.373 --> 02:21:44.207
We won! We won!

02:21:44.375 --> 02:21:46.626
Ellen, we won! Aren't you happy?

02:21:46.794 --> 02:21:52.632
Oh, my God, Ellen, you have to be happy.
He's innocent. Carl Lee is innocent.

02:21:54.009 --> 02:21:55.343
He's coming home.

02:21:55.511 --> 02:21:56.803
Jake.

02:21:58.097 --> 02:21:59.931
That was....

02:22:00.641 --> 02:22:02.475
That was....

02:22:03.686 --> 02:22:06.020
Hey, I'm one of the bad guys, remember?

02:22:08.649 --> 02:22:11.943
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

02:22:21.662 --> 02:22:23.913
Freddie Lee Cobb!

02:22:26.625 --> 02:22:29.043
We got something to talk about.

02:22:29.211 --> 02:22:30.753
Hastings...

02:22:30.921 --> 02:22:33.506
...you belong over there with them.

02:22:35.134 --> 02:22:36.968
Get over.

02:22:48.647 --> 02:22:50.523
Congratulations, counselor.

02:22:50.691 --> 02:22:52.316
Thank you.

02:23:13.756 --> 02:23:16.048
You must be overwhelmed right now.

02:23:45.204 --> 02:23:47.288
- Give me--
- After you--

02:23:47.456 --> 02:23:48.831
Yeah.

02:23:51.627 --> 02:23:53.753
- Was I good or what?
- All right.

02:23:53.921 --> 02:23:57.048
Oh. Ha-ha-ha.

02:24:04.598 --> 02:24:05.932
Here you go.

02:24:06.099 --> 02:24:09.644
- Carl Lee. Look.
- What?

02:24:33.544 --> 02:24:35.044
Well.

02:24:35.212 --> 02:24:36.254
Hello.

02:24:36.421 --> 02:24:37.505
- Hi.
- Hi there.

02:24:37.673 --> 02:24:39.090
Hannah, this is Miss Hailey.

02:24:39.258 --> 02:24:40.299
- This is Hannah.
- Hi.

02:24:40.467 --> 02:24:43.427
- Hi, Hannah. Ain't she so pretty.
- Thank you.

02:24:43.595 --> 02:24:46.222
- Brought you some peach cobbler.
- Oh, thank you.

02:24:46.390 --> 02:24:48.266
Come on in. Come in.

02:24:50.060 --> 02:24:51.686
Howdy.

02:25:01.446 --> 02:25:03.865
Hannah, this is my daughter, Tonya.

02:25:04.032 --> 02:25:07.201
- Hi, Tonya.
- Hi, nice to meet you, Hannah.

02:25:10.747 --> 02:25:12.832
Just thought our kids
could play together.

